-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612514\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dbd1665702611680.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dbd1665702611680.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dbd1665702611680.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dbd1665702611680\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Horizontal Scaling (\n                              Hscale)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property determines how the image is horizontally scaled; valid only for <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Image</span> data types. Default value is <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">100</code> (percent).\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__p_d99557e1_d99558e1_d99559e1\">\n         \n                                Hscale\n                                <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Percentage</var> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Auto</code>\n</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__table_d11549e1_d11550e1_d11551e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__table_d11549e1_d11550e1_d11551e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Value</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__table_d11549e1_d11550e1_d11551e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dbd1665702611680__table_d11549e1_d11550e1_d11551e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Percentage</var>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dbd1665702611680__table_d11549e1_d11550e1_d11551e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Positive or negative integer from <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> through <code class=\"ph codeph\">10000</code>. Negative values enable you to mirror images.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dbd1665702611680__table_d11549e1_d11550e1_d11551e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Auto</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dbd1665702611680__table_d11549e1_d11550e1_d11551e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Scale the image horizontally to fit the widget. Instead of preserving the aspect ratio, it stretches the image to fit the widget.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__section_ubm_wpj_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d305430e146\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__p_d99563e1_d99564e1_d99565e1\">If the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Preserve Aspect</span> property\n            is <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>, the larger of <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Horizontal Scaling</span> and\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Vertical Scale</span> properties is ignored.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__section_wfz_xpj_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d305430e167\">Command Button</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__p_d99569e1_d99570e1_d99571e1\">For command buttons, this property only takes effect\n            if the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Representation</span> property is set to\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">Uniface</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__section_ifp_zpj_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d305430e182\">Example: Setting in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__p_d99575e1_d99576e1_d99577e1\">Set the scale to 80 percent:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__pre_cjg_cqj_swb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$fieldproperties(FLD1) = \"hscale=80\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__section_tbk_dqj_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d305430e195\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__ul_y3h_2qj_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__li_d40340e1_d40341e1_d40342e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujj1665702610581.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujj1665702610581.html\" title=\"Area frames are objects that can be used to group or separate the contents of a Form component.\">Area Frames and Lines</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__li_d40343e1_d40344e1_d40345e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iic1718342502908.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iic1718342502908.html\" title=\"The udefentity widget is the default widget for entities in form components. It is a multi-occurrence list, with a minimum of one occurrence, in which fields can be freely arranged. Uniface provides a default logical widget called DefEntity that is mapped to this widget.\">udefentity (Default Entity Widget )</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__li_d40346e1_d40347e1_d40348e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrc1665702631553.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrc1665702631553.html\" title=\"The CommandButton is a logical widget that enables a user to initiate an action by clicking the button.\">CommandButton</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__li_d40349e1_d40350e1_d40351e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rgn1665702634165.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rgn1665702634165.html\" title=\"Image to use as the background image on the map widget.\">Image Name</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__ul_ijh_2qj_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__li_d40352e1_d40353e1_d40354e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ula1665702613468.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ula1665702613468.html\" title=\"An Entity defines a logical data aggregation. It usually represents a relational database table, but it is possible to define non-database entities for transient data, reusable user interface controls, or other application structures.\">Entities</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dbd1665702611680__li_d40355e1_d40356e1_d40357e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"scc1665702611448.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/scc1665702611448.html\" title=\"Image used as background for the application window, form, or entity. This property can be set in ProcScript.\">Background Image (BackImage)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sup1665702611757.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Vertical Scaling ( Vscale)</a><p>This property determines how the image is scaled vertically; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612514\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612514\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale) This property determines how the image is horizontally scaled; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent). Hscale = Percentage | Auto Value Description Percentage Positive or negative integer from 1 through 10000 . Negative values enable you to mirror images. Auto Scale the image horizontally to fit the widget. Instead of preserving the aspect ratio, it stretches the image to fit the widget. Description If the Preserve Aspect property is True , the larger of Horizontal Scaling and Vertical Scale properties is ignored. Command Button For command buttons, this property only takes effect if the Representation property is set to Uniface . Example: Setting in ProcScript Set the scale to 80 percent: $fieldproperties(FLD1) = \"hscale=80\" Copy Applies To Area Frames and Lines udefentity (Default Entity Widget ) CommandButton Image Name Entities Background Image (BackImage) Related Links Vertical Scaling ( Vscale) This property determines how the image is scaled vertically; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}